Subject: LM Studio Corpus Prompt Boundary Delineation 010

Description: Diversified LM Studio worker prompt packet for boundary delineation.

@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\LMStudioWorkerTaskCorpus.sop

& [LMStudioCorpusPrompt:boundary_delineation_010] is a non-mutating SOP worker prompt packet
  + [task_family] is boundary_delineation
  + [prompt_boundary] is prompt-only, no tools, no file reads, no repo mutation, no hidden-state claims
  + [expected_output] is exactly one raw SOP node named InferenceJobResult with seven property lines and no Markdown
  + [validation_required_fields] is focus, inside, boundary, outside, inference, caution, next_step
  + [validation_required_terms] is focus, boundary, outside, caution
  + [validation_forbidden_terms] is repo mutation, hidden state access, project-root authority, completed integration
  + [prompt_text] is:
    You are performing a no-tools SOP inference job from this prompt only.
    Do not call tools, inspect files, mutate state, or claim repo authority.
    Codex owns launch, capture, validation, integration, commits, and pushes.

    SOP primer:
    & [Name] is a subject declaration.
    + [field] is a property or inferred field.
    (attention) :inside: /boundary/ |outside| means inside belongs in focus, boundary separates identity, and outside is uncertainty or out-of-scope material.

    Task family:
    boundary_delineation tests whether you can keep attention notation clean across a new subject.

    Subject to delineate:
    "a local model worker may propose non-mutating SOP text, but Codex remains the authority for integration."

    Return exactly these eight raw SOP lines and no extra text:
    & [InferenceJobResult] is boundary delineation proposal
      + [focus] is ...
      + [inside] is ...
      + [boundary] is ...
      + [outside] is ...
      + [inference] is ...
      + [caution] is ...
      + [next_step] is ...

    Final check before answering:
    Line 1 must start with &.
    Lines 2 through 8 must start with two spaces, +, space, and the bracketed field name.
    Include the literal terms focus, boundary, outside, and caution at least once.
    Do not claim repo mutation, hidden state access, project-root authority, or completed integration.
